{#
  Shared bottom of the floating sidebar menu: the "New workspace" CTA, a
  horizontal divider, a "Settings" entry, and the "Manage account(s)" / "Log in"
  entry. Rendered inside Chrome.jinja (browser-mode inline sidebar) and
  Sidebar.jinja (the sidebar page loaded into the shared modal WebContentsView in
  Electron) so the markup and classes live in one place (the icons are shared
  Icon16 glyphs -- ``plus``, ``settings``, ``user``). The button
  ids (#sidebar-new-workspace, #sidebar-settings, #sidebar-account) are wired up
  in chrome.js and sidebar.js respectively; the #sidebar-account-label span is
  updated by both scripts when the auth status changes.

  These elements are direct flex children of #sidebar-menu (JinjaX
  inlines the component), so the panel's ``gap-0.5`` (2px) supplies the
  spacing between every entry -- including the 2px above and below the
  bare divider line, which therefore needs no padding of its own.
#}
<button id="sidebar-new-workspace"
        type="button"
        class="sidebar-action group flex items-center gap-2 h-8 px-2 rounded-md cursor-pointer type-body text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-fill-hover bg-transparent border-0 text-left">
  <Icon16 name="plus" extra="shrink-0" />
  <span>New workspace</span>
</button>
<div class="h-px bg-subtle"></div>
<button id="sidebar-settings"
        type="button"
        class="sidebar-action group flex items-center gap-2 h-8 px-2 rounded-md cursor-pointer type-body text-primary hover:bg-fill-hover bg-transparent border-0 text-left">
  <Icon16 name="settings" extra="shrink-0" />
  <span>Settings</span>
</button>
<button id="sidebar-account"
        type="button"
        class="sidebar-action group flex items-center gap-2 h-8 px-2 rounded-md cursor-pointer type-body text-primary hover:bg-fill-hover bg-transparent border-0 text-left"
        title="">
  <Icon16 name="user" extra="shrink-0" />
  <span id="sidebar-account-label">Log in</span>
</button>
